Uttar Pradesh
Dec 15, 2014
Abuse
Description:
			A five-year-old student of a private school today died after he was allegedly beaten by his teacher in Rath village here, police said.

According to an FIR filed by the parents of the minor, Araj, studying in kindergarten, was beaten by a teacher, following which they got a call from the school that they should come to pick up their ward as he was ill, SP Rural Brijesh Kumar Srivastava said.

When the parents reached the school, they found Araj unconscious and rushed him to a hospital, where he died, the SP said.

The cause of his death could not be ascertained yet and police is awaiting the post-mortem report in this connection, he said.

An FIR has been registered against the magager of the school.


